clean certificate
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a certificate issued to a property by sheep inspectors [mid-late 1800s] if sheep on the property were found to be free of scab.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
